Choose a file that contain rows of problem scores or feedback in the following comma-separated format:

<div class="code">
  <p class="code">
    <code>Andrew ID, <% @assessment.problems.each { |p| %><%= p.name %> Score/Feedback, <% } %>Grade Type</code>
  </p>
  
  <p>All columns are mandatory. An empty cell will leave the existing value unmodified. Valid values for Grade Type are <code>normal</code>, <code>zeroed</code>, <code>excused</code>, and empty.</p>
</div>

<%= form_for :upload, :html => { :multipart => true } do |f| %>
  <div class="controls">
    <%= f.file_field :file %>

    <div class="radio">
      <label>
        <%= f.radio_button :data_type, "scores", { :checked => true } %>
        Scores
      </label>
    </div>

    <div class="radio">
      <label>
        <%= f.radio_button :data_type, "feedback" %>
        Feedback <span class="info">use escape characters in place of newlines (\n) and tabs (\t)</span>
      </label>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p>
    We will show you a preview of the uploaded data before it used to update grades. The update will occur as a 
    <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Database_transaction#Transactional_databases">transaction</a>,
    allowing you to correct errors and re-submit.
  </p>
  <%= f.submit 'Start' %>
<% end %>
